Racism is not as simple as &ldquo;hating all black people.&rdquo;
It&rsquo;s more accurate to say that racism is when one views one race as &ldquo;innocent until proven guilty,&rdquo; and another as &ldquo;guilty until proven innocent.&rdquo;
The fact that someone has black friends doesn&rsquo;t say much, because it could be a case of &ldquo;innocent until proven guilty,&rdquo; but it could also be a case of &ldquo;guilty until proven innocent.&rdquo;
Whether or not someone has black friends doesn&rsquo;t really say anything one way or another.

If we&rsquo;re not going to delve into the entire failure of Reconstruction to put Black people on anywhere near an equal footing in our society&hellip;
The first thing we need to understand is the cost of credit, i.e., the interest rates on loans. Black people being systematically deprived from being lent to means that the community will have more difficulty building up wealth.
The most recent is by not being privy to Federal Housing Association (FHA) loans in the post World War II economic boom, Black people were prevented from accumulating capital in home ownership.

